assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: TATSUTA Electric Wire and Cable Co., Ltd. engages in the manufacture and sale of electric wires/cables, electronic materials, and sensor and medical products in Japan. The company provides electric wires and cables for power distribution, and nuclear power plants; high-strength, instrument, broadcasting, high-frequency coaxial cables, as well as customized cable terminals. It also offers electronic materials comprising electromagnetic interference (EMI) shielding films for FPC applications and related products; films for FFC applications; functional pastes; and bonding wires, including gold/gold bumping, silver, copper, and palladium wires. In addition, the company provides sensor products, such as water leakage detection sensors, water leakage detection systems, flame-retardant, chemical-resistant leakage sensors, and sheet sensors; and medical equipment products, which include liquid leakage sensors, IV counter, liquid control systems for artificial dialysis equipment, optical fiber interference tomography meter for OCT applications, and electric wires for medical applications. Further, it offers optical fiber components, as well as environmental analysis services. TATSUTA Electric Wire and Cable Co., Ltd. was founded in 1945 and is headquartered in Higashiosaka, Japan.
